18
00:00:12,540 --> 00:00:15,540
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:17,564 --> 00:00:19,191
<i>Clone crisis!</i>

20
00:00:19,274 --> 00:00:22,068
<i>After the mysterious death
of his friend Tup,</i>

21
00:00:22,152 --> 00:00:24,821
<i>ARC Trooper Fives
embarked on an investigation,</i>

22
00:00:24,905 --> 00:00:27,115
<i>which led to the discovery
of a hidden chip</i>

23
00:00:27,199 --> 00:00:31,453
<i>which is placed inside clone troopers
when they are still embryos.</i>

24
00:00:31,536 --> 00:00:34,915
<i>The Kaminoan scientist Nala Se
claims the chip is harmless</i>

25
00:00:34,998 --> 00:00:38,710
<i>and is meant to restrain the clones
from violent unpredictable action.</i>

26
00:00:39,211 --> 00:00:40,879
<i>Fives claims otherwise,</i>

27
00:00:40,962 --> 00:00:43,089
<i>and has convinced
Jedi Master Shaak Ti</i>

28
00:00:43,173 --> 00:00:44,716
<i>to allow him to plead his case</i>

29
00:00:44,799 --> 00:00:48,511
<i>directly to Supreme Chancellor
Palpatine on Coruscant.</i>

30
00:00:53,683 --> 00:00:54,768
Attention.

31
00:00:54,851 --> 00:00:57,103
Please be advised
we have arrived at Coruscant

32
00:00:57,187 --> 00:01:00,315
<i>and will be touching down
at our destination shortly.</i>

33
00:01:19,292 --> 00:01:21,044
No. Wait.

34
00:01:23,213 --> 00:01:25,423
No. What was that?

35
00:01:26,508 --> 00:01:27,801
What did you do?

36
00:01:27,884 --> 00:01:29,427
You drugged me.

37
00:01:55,370 --> 00:01:59,666
Greetings, Master Jedi.
The Chancellor is waiting inside.

38
00:02:00,917 --> 00:02:03,878
Tup... The mission...

39
00:02:05,088 --> 00:02:06,548
AZI-3...

40
00:02:17,225 --> 00:02:20,812
Master Shaak Ti,
it is good to see you again.

41
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:25,942
I trust you've kept this matter
extremely confidential.

42
00:02:26,568 --> 00:02:28,403
Of course, Chancellor.

43
00:02:29,321 --> 00:02:30,530
Good.

44
00:02:30,613 --> 00:02:34,242
So this is the clone
who has caused so much alarm?

45
00:02:36,369 --> 00:02:39,080
No... No, you drugged me.

46
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,041
She...

47
00:02:41,124 --> 00:02:43,918
There, there, soldier,
don't strain yourself.

48
00:02:44,711 --> 00:02:45,712
Sir.

49
00:02:46,463 --> 00:02:49,090
Guards, let him down, please.

50
00:02:51,426 --> 00:02:55,138
Now, Trooper,
what brings you before me?

51
00:02:55,930 --> 00:02:57,807
The chips, Chancellor.

52
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,601
Chips?

53
00:02:59,726 --> 00:03:02,854
These were removed
from both clone troopers.

54
00:03:03,146 --> 00:03:07,025
Clone Trooper Fives claims
they are the cause of the problem.

55
00:03:07,108 --> 00:03:10,362
Those are inhibitor chips,
which are placed in clones

56
00:03:10,445 --> 00:03:13,782
to make them less aggressive
and more compliant to orders.

57
00:03:13,865 --> 00:03:15,700
I tried to explain to this clone

58
00:03:15,784 --> 00:03:18,203
that they are placed in them
for his own good,

59
00:03:18,286 --> 00:03:20,997
but he removed his chip nonetheless.

60
00:03:21,081 --> 00:03:22,540
Our own good?

61
00:03:22,624 --> 00:03:26,211
This thing they put in us
malfunctioned in Clone Trooper Tup.

62
00:03:26,294 --> 00:03:28,713
I removed his and analyzed it.

63
00:03:28,797 --> 00:03:30,298
There were signs of rapid decay.

64
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:34,636
And we're positive
this has nothing to do with a virus?

65
00:03:35,804 --> 00:03:40,266
No, we still do not know for sure
what caused Trooper Tup to kill.

66
00:03:40,350 --> 00:03:42,394
We only know that his chip failed.

67
00:03:42,477 --> 00:03:45,688
And now this clone
has removed his own chip,

68
00:03:45,772 --> 00:03:49,234
which makes him
a risk to himself and others.

69
00:03:49,317 --> 00:03:51,236
I'm not at risk.

70
00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:53,405
Sir, they're covering something up,
I know it.

71
00:03:54,239 --> 00:03:56,574
If it's not them,
then it's a Separatist plot.

72
00:03:56,658 --> 00:04:01,079
They use this chip against us
to make us more violent than less.

73
00:04:01,162 --> 00:04:03,581
That's why Tup killed General Tiplar.

74
00:04:03,665 --> 00:04:08,753
A Separatist plot
from before the war even started?

75
00:04:08,837 --> 00:04:12,966
That seems unlikely,
don't you agree, Master Shaak Ti?

76
00:04:13,049 --> 00:04:16,761
It does, Chancellor.
It seems very unlikely.

77
00:04:16,845 --> 00:04:19,013
It is absolutely impossible.

78
00:04:19,097 --> 00:04:23,101
What we have here is a single
malfunction to one clone's inhibitor chip

79
00:04:23,184 --> 00:04:26,354
caused by a virus,
Separatist plot or not.

80
00:04:26,896 --> 00:04:28,565
Perhaps it would be best

81
00:04:28,648 --> 00:04:33,945
if Clone Trooper Fives and I
discussed this without your presence.

82
00:04:34,028 --> 00:04:36,281
Chancellor, I must object.

83
00:04:36,364 --> 00:04:39,200
Please, Master Jedi, trust me.

84
00:04:39,701 --> 00:04:43,788
I will not be alone.
I have my security here.

85
00:04:44,330 --> 00:04:49,043
I want this soldier to feel
he is having a fair say in this matter.

86
00:05:01,181 --> 00:05:02,390
Now,

87
00:05:04,726 --> 00:05:06,478
where were we?

88
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:18,281
No! Let me go!

89
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,450
Guards!

90
00:05:23,703 --> 00:05:24,913
No! You!

91
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:32,045
He tried to kill me. It was so sudden.

92
00:05:38,801 --> 00:05:40,178
You were right, Doctor,

93
00:05:40,261 --> 00:05:42,931
he must have gone mad
without his chip.

94
00:05:45,308 --> 00:05:48,144
You have done all you can, Doctor.

95
00:05:49,062 --> 00:05:51,397
I trust you will keep these safe.

96
00:05:51,731 --> 00:05:53,608
Of course, Chancellor.

97
00:06:03,618 --> 00:06:04,744
Fives, stop!

98
00:06:05,328 --> 00:06:06,496
Fives!

99
00:06:20,218 --> 00:06:21,719
Close the blast doors!

100
00:06:41,489 --> 00:06:45,618
I can't believe Fives would try
to assassinate the Chancellor.

101
00:06:45,702 --> 00:06:49,455
The Kaminoans feel a virus
corrupted the Clone's inhibitor chip,

102
00:06:49,539 --> 00:06:51,791
which has led to this behavior.

103
00:06:51,874 --> 00:06:55,336
ARC Trooper Fives feels
he is the victim of a plot,

104
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:57,589
Separatist or otherwise.

105
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:59,674
<i>All security and clone forces
on Coruscant</i>

106
00:06:59,757 --> 00:07:01,759
<i>have been ordered to join the manhunt.</i>

107
00:07:01,843 --> 00:07:04,012
<i>The Chancellor has been
moved to his Senate quarters</i>

108
00:07:04,095 --> 00:07:05,930
<i>and the perimeter has been secured.</i>

109
00:07:06,014 --> 00:07:10,268
<i>However, Jedi involvement
has not been requested.</i>

110
00:07:10,351 --> 00:07:12,729
That's a little odd, isn't it?

111
00:07:14,439 --> 00:07:16,941
<i>Discover the truth we must.</i>

112
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:21,070
<i>If there is a plot involving the clones,
we must get to the bottom of it.</i>

113
00:07:22,322 --> 00:07:24,949
<i>We will investigate quietly, undercover.</i>

114
00:07:25,033 --> 00:07:28,036
<i>We must make sure
this clone is not killed.</i>

115
00:07:28,119 --> 00:07:29,871
I'll handle this investigation.

116
00:07:30,330 --> 00:07:34,375
Fives was part of the 501 st.
If Rex and I find him, he'll trust us.

117
00:07:34,876 --> 00:07:38,671
Be wary.
Since he removed his inhibitor chip,

118
00:07:39,047 --> 00:07:42,383
Fives may no longer be
the man you once knew.

119
00:08:19,462 --> 00:08:21,631
-Here you go.
-Thank you, ladies.

120
00:08:21,714 --> 00:08:23,800
Have a good time on Coruscant, now.

121
00:08:23,883 --> 00:08:25,343
Thank you.

122
00:08:28,513 --> 00:08:30,431
Hey, pal, where to?

123
00:08:30,515 --> 00:08:32,183
Take me to 79's.

124
00:08:32,266 --> 00:08:33,976
The clone bar?

125
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:35,937
You're a clone, eh?

126
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:37,730
Look, just shut up and drive.

127
00:08:37,814 --> 00:08:39,649
Okay, you got it.

128
00:08:53,746 --> 00:08:56,749
So, heading out
for a little fun on the town, eh?

129
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:59,335
I didn't know clones could have fun.

130
00:08:59,419 --> 00:09:01,671
There's a lot you don't know
about clones.

131
00:09:01,754 --> 00:09:03,297
No one knows.

132
00:09:04,257 --> 00:09:07,552
Very mysterious, eh?
I like a good mystery.

133
00:09:07,635 --> 00:09:11,848
Yeah? You ever hear the one
about the people engineered to kill,

134
00:09:11,931 --> 00:09:13,641
engineered to kill their best friends,

135
00:09:13,725 --> 00:09:16,728
their leaders,
and they don't even know it?

136
00:09:16,811 --> 00:09:20,606
I'm a cab driver, pal.
I hear stories like that all the time.

137
00:09:41,711 --> 00:09:44,046
Hey. You paying for this ride or what?

138
00:09:45,506 --> 00:09:47,175
Bill it to the Republic.

139
00:09:47,508 --> 00:09:50,595
"Bill it to the Republic."
Good one, brother.

140
00:09:50,678 --> 00:09:52,847
Lousy cheap clones!

141
00:09:53,306 --> 00:09:56,476
It's your credit, pal.
You're paying for this.

142
00:09:59,145 --> 00:10:01,105
Your mother's a droid.

143
00:10:02,982 --> 00:10:05,777
-Get out of here.
-Droid lover!

144
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:08,112
Come on, brother, let's go inside.

145
00:10:08,196 --> 00:10:10,907
Corporal, that's a nice hat you got there.

146
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:12,492
Mind if I see it?

147
00:10:12,575 --> 00:10:14,869
Sure. Yeah. Sure, you got it.

148
00:10:20,249 --> 00:10:22,043
To the Republic!

149
00:10:22,710 --> 00:10:24,295
Can I get you fellas anything?

150
00:10:24,378 --> 00:10:26,422
I think it's time for another round.

151
00:10:26,506 --> 00:10:28,174
Hey, bartender!

152
00:10:28,257 --> 00:10:30,593
Hey, see you around, brother.

153
00:10:45,942 --> 00:10:47,568
Kix, Jesse.

154
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:03,668
To the 212th!

155
00:11:03,751 --> 00:11:05,711
Down the hatch, boys!

156
00:11:14,095 --> 00:11:15,930
Fan out and check IDs.

157
00:11:30,236 --> 00:11:33,781
So, I guess the 501 st
is back on Coruscant.

158
00:11:34,782 --> 00:11:38,369
Yeah, we just got back
from Ringo Vinda.

159
00:11:38,452 --> 00:11:40,955
The strangest thing
happened out there.

160
00:11:41,706 --> 00:11:44,083
Yeah, I know.

161
00:11:46,127 --> 00:11:47,461
Fives?

162
00:11:48,212 --> 00:11:49,380
What's going on?

163
00:11:49,463 --> 00:11:51,716
They say you tried
to assassinate the Chancellor!

164
00:11:51,799 --> 00:11:54,510
And that you're infected
with that virus that killed Tup.

165
00:11:54,594 --> 00:11:56,387
I don't have time to explain right now.

166
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:59,849
All I can tell you
is that I'm being framed.

167
00:11:59,932 --> 00:12:03,811
All of us, even the Jedi,
are in grave danger.

168
00:12:03,895 --> 00:12:07,064
But what can I do, Fives?
How can I help?

169
00:12:07,148 --> 00:12:09,609
I need to talk to Rex, or...

170
00:12:09,692 --> 00:12:11,110
Or General Skywalker.

171
00:12:11,193 --> 00:12:14,572
Well, they've been tasked with
finding you. Just turn yourself in!

172
00:12:14,655 --> 00:12:18,200
No! No, I'll never get to them.

173
00:12:18,284 --> 00:12:19,493
You don't understand.

174
00:12:19,785 --> 00:12:23,164
What I'm mixed up in,
it goes all the way to the top.

175
00:12:23,748 --> 00:12:26,584
The highest levels
are involved in the conspiracy.

176
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:30,588
I have to talk to General Skywalker
and Rex directly, alone.

177
00:12:30,671 --> 00:12:35,134
Look, I can contact Rex, but I can't
guarantee he'll bring the General.

178
00:12:35,509 --> 00:12:37,094
Good, good, good.

179
00:12:37,178 --> 00:12:39,472
Thanks, Kix. I appreciate it.

180
00:12:39,555 --> 00:12:41,849
Here. Here are the coordinates.

181
00:12:43,517 --> 00:12:45,853
Just make sure he meets me there.

182
00:12:46,437 --> 00:12:49,273
Right. Good luck, Fives.

183
00:12:50,066 --> 00:12:51,943
Identification, please.

184
00:12:52,026 --> 00:12:53,361
Have you seen this clone?

185
00:12:54,862 --> 00:12:56,364
No, sir. I haven't seen him.

186
00:12:56,447 --> 00:12:57,990
All right. Move along.

187
00:13:06,165 --> 00:13:07,625
Identification, please.

188
00:13:18,678 --> 00:13:20,471
All right, you guys check out.

189
00:13:20,554 --> 00:13:21,889
Move along.

190
00:14:37,965 --> 00:14:42,136
Sir, the fugitive clone has been spotted
by one of our probes in sector I-9.

191
00:15:03,282 --> 00:15:05,785
Well, these are the coordinates
Kix gave us.

192
00:15:05,868 --> 00:15:07,953
Let's hope Fives is inside.

193
00:15:08,037 --> 00:15:09,997
I hope he knows what he's doing.

194
00:15:24,637 --> 00:15:26,097
Fives?

195
00:15:26,180 --> 00:15:27,556
Fives, we're here.

196
00:15:29,391 --> 00:15:31,894
Come on out,
we just want to talk to you.

197
00:15:38,609 --> 00:15:42,363
General Skywalker, thank you.
Thank you for trusting me.

198
00:15:43,656 --> 00:15:45,366
Have you come without troops?

199
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,493
We have.

200
00:15:48,494 --> 00:15:50,246
Put down your weapons, then.

201
00:15:51,247 --> 00:15:53,124
I don't think so, Fives.

202
00:15:53,207 --> 00:15:54,667
Please, sir.

203
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:56,627
Please, I'm unarmed.

204
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:03,300
All right, I'm putting my pistols down.

205
00:16:06,637 --> 00:16:08,764
What are we here for, Fives?

206
00:16:10,141 --> 00:16:11,725
I need your help.

207
00:16:12,143 --> 00:16:15,312
I know you do. We know you're not well.

208
00:16:15,396 --> 00:16:17,523
It's been rough for you
these past couple days.

209
00:16:17,606 --> 00:16:19,150
I'm not crazy!

210
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:21,485
Please. Please, just...

211
00:16:21,569 --> 00:16:24,405
Just hear what I have to say.

212
00:16:27,199 --> 00:16:29,827
We're here to help you, Fives.
Just come with us.

213
00:16:30,411 --> 00:16:32,246
Let us take you back to the Temple.

214
00:16:35,291 --> 00:16:36,584
No!

215
00:16:38,252 --> 00:16:41,755
I just need you to listen to me. Please.

216
00:16:42,006 --> 00:16:44,425
I'm not really sure
we have any other choice.

217
00:16:44,508 --> 00:16:47,511
I was framed because I know the truth.

218
00:16:48,596 --> 00:16:51,932
The truth about a plot,
a massive deception!

219
00:16:52,641 --> 00:16:54,101
By whom?

220
00:16:54,602 --> 00:16:57,897
Well, there's a sinister plot in the works
against the Jedi.

221
00:16:57,980 --> 00:16:59,106
I have proof of it.

222
00:16:59,190 --> 00:17:01,859
I can prove that everything
that I know is true

223
00:17:01,942 --> 00:17:03,402
beyond a shadow of a doubt!

224
00:17:04,445 --> 00:17:06,405
Show me the evidence.

225
00:17:07,698 --> 00:17:10,326
The evidence is in here.

226
00:17:10,409 --> 00:17:13,954
It's in here. It's in all of us, every clone!

227
00:17:14,580 --> 00:17:15,706
What is it?

228
00:17:16,248 --> 00:17:20,211
Organic chips,
built into our genetic code

229
00:17:20,294 --> 00:17:23,422
to make us do
whatever someone wants,

230
00:17:23,505 --> 00:17:25,507
even kill the Jedi.

231
00:17:25,591 --> 00:17:27,509
It's all in here!

232
00:17:29,887 --> 00:17:33,933
Let's just get you some help first,
then we can review everything.

233
00:17:34,016 --> 00:17:36,769
It'll be okay, Fives. We'll sort this out.

234
00:17:37,561 --> 00:17:39,438
You don't believe me!

235
00:17:42,983 --> 00:17:46,195
We're closing in on the target.
Everyone be ready.

236
00:17:47,738 --> 00:17:52,076
Fives, we are listening to you.
We only want to help.

237
00:17:52,159 --> 00:17:56,664
How do I know you're not tricking me?
How do I know it won't be a trap?

238
00:17:56,747 --> 00:18:00,000
The Chancellor will try to kill me!
I promise you that!

239
00:18:00,084 --> 00:18:01,168
The Chancellor?

240
00:18:05,756 --> 00:18:07,216
He's in on it!

241
00:18:08,008 --> 00:18:12,054
I don't know to what extent.
But I know he orchestrated much of this.

242
00:18:12,137 --> 00:18:13,973
He told me in the medical bay!

243
00:18:14,265 --> 00:18:17,309
He told you?
When you tried to assassinate him?

244
00:18:17,768 --> 00:18:19,603
You have gone too far, Fives.

245
00:18:19,687 --> 00:18:22,106
The Chancellor is incapable
of what you claim.

246
00:18:22,189 --> 00:18:23,232
He is!

247
00:18:23,315 --> 00:18:25,734
I swear to you, General.
You have no idea...

248
00:18:25,818 --> 00:18:28,362
Stand down, soldier! Stand down !
Get on your knees!

249
00:18:28,445 --> 00:18:30,030
No! No! No! Stay back!

250
00:18:30,447 --> 00:18:31,991
Don't do it! Don't do it, soldier!

251
00:18:32,074 --> 00:18:33,701
Get away from me!

252
00:18:33,784 --> 00:18:35,244
Fives, no!

253
00:18:45,754 --> 00:18:47,423
Fives!

254
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:48,799
Fives!

255
00:18:48,882 --> 00:18:51,385
-Fives!
-Get this ray shield off!

256
00:18:53,512 --> 00:18:55,222
Fives!

257
00:18:55,306 --> 00:18:56,432
Brother!

258
00:18:56,849 --> 00:18:58,726
Call for help! We need a medic!

259
00:19:01,061 --> 00:19:02,479
Rex...

260
00:19:02,563 --> 00:19:03,772
Fives.

261
00:19:03,856 --> 00:19:08,277
This... It's bigger than any of us...

262
00:19:08,902 --> 00:19:12,072
Than anything I could have imagined.

263
00:19:13,699 --> 00:19:15,951
I never meant to...

264
00:19:17,286 --> 00:19:19,246
I only wanted to do my duty.

265
00:19:23,542 --> 00:19:24,752
Brother...

266
00:19:24,835 --> 00:19:26,628
Fives, stay with me, Fives!

267
00:19:26,712 --> 00:19:27,838
Fives!

268
00:19:27,921 --> 00:19:29,423
The mission...

269
00:19:30,632 --> 00:19:32,343
The nightmares...

270
00:19:32,426 --> 00:19:37,264
They're finally over.

271
00:19:40,476 --> 00:19:41,852
Fives?

272
00:19:41,935 --> 00:19:44,396
No, Fives... Come on, Fives.

273
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,440
Don't go! Stay with me. Stay with me.

274
00:19:46,523 --> 00:19:48,359
Fives! Fives!

275
00:19:48,442 --> 00:19:49,818
Don't go.

276
00:19:51,737 --> 00:19:52,863
No!

277
00:19:53,947 --> 00:19:55,824
Oh, no.

278
00:20:09,463 --> 00:20:12,299
A tragic situation, indeed.

279
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:16,720
About the clone's breakdowns,
have we discovered any new evidence?

280
00:20:16,804 --> 00:20:20,933
I've had my own personal doctors
examine both bodies.

281
00:20:21,016 --> 00:20:26,146
It appears Nala Se did miss something
in her examination.

282
00:20:26,230 --> 00:20:28,482
Another cause your doctors found?

283
00:20:31,151 --> 00:20:35,864
A parasite, native to Ringo Vinda.

284
00:20:35,948 --> 00:20:39,284
Probably in a canteen of water
they both shared.

285
00:20:39,368 --> 00:20:42,287
It did cause the inhibitors to decay,

286
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:44,790
once the parasite had taken hold.

287
00:20:44,873 --> 00:20:47,084
It is very rare.

288
00:20:47,167 --> 00:20:49,711
However, just to be cautious,

289
00:20:49,795 --> 00:20:55,300
we have prepared an inoculation
for every clone trooper in our army.

290
00:20:55,676 --> 00:20:58,345
So, I guess it's over, then?

291
00:20:58,804 --> 00:21:04,518
Yes, we can finally put this
whole wretched situation behind us.

292
00:21:04,977 --> 00:21:08,772
We must direct our attention
back to the war at hand.

293
00:21:08,856 --> 00:21:15,028
Each day we grow
closer and closer to victory.

294
00:21:23,162 --> 00:21:27,916
<i>Lord Tyranus, have you received
the inhibitor chip that you requested?</i>

295
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:30,127
I have indeed.

296
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:32,212
You have done well, Doctor.

297
00:21:42,890 --> 00:21:45,559
Our plan has gone
undiscovered, Master.

298
00:21:46,435 --> 00:21:52,441
The clone in question is now dead
and the Jedi still suspect nothing.

299
00:21:52,524 --> 00:21:54,401
<i>Good.</i>

300
00:21:54,485 --> 00:21:57,362
<i>Destroy all evidence.</i>

301
00:21:57,446 --> 00:22:02,701
<i>When the time comes,
no one will be able to stop our plan</i>

302
00:22:02,784 --> 00:22:07,039
<i>to execute Order 66.</i>

303
00:22:07,063 --> 00:22:12,063
http://hiqve.com/

